About 2,200 vulnerable people, e.g the poor,  widows and orphans are said to have received a cash gift of N5, 000 each in Daura local government area of Katsina State. Personal assistant and special adviser on labour matters to the minister of aviation, Aliyu Shargale, revealed this in an exclusive interview with our correspondent in Katsina yesterday. He said the cash donation was to reduce the suffering of the people who were observing the lockdown order. “The minister sent us with a cash donation of N12 million to present to the people of Daura local government area, the money will be shared according to the 11 wards in Daura and each ward would receive one N1million and there are a certain category of people who  will share the remaining N1million.From the eleven million naira meant for the wards, each person is entitled to N5, 000 in an envelope,” he said. He further explained that the money as directed was handed to the local government area  COVID -19 committee set up by the state government, comprising a member of the state house of assembly, traditional rulers, religious leaders among others. 